
 [CentOS]
 	
	/etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-*		# /usr/share-doc/initscripts-*/sysconfig.txt [section /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-<interface-name>]

	 #Configuation directives and accepted values
  	BOOTPROTO={static|dhcp}
		NETMASK={mask}
		GATEWAY={addr}

	 #restart network service
	 	service network restart
	



 [Debian]
 /etc/network/intefaces contains network interfaces configuration information for the ifup(8) and ifdown(8) commands.
 iface
 mapping
 auto
 allow-
 source
 source-directory

 Lines beginning with the word "auto" are used to identify the physical intefaces to be brought up when ifup is run with the -a option.
